text: Inger's tree frog or Robert Inger's tree frog (Rhacophorus verrucopus) is a frog. It lives in Vietnam in forests where the tree branches come together like the roof of a house. Scientists have seen it between 400 and 1700 meters above sea level. Scientists believe it may also live in Laos. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Rhacophorus robertingeri
